        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(ui): add KaTeX math rendering support",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdd KaTeX-based mathematical formula rendering to OpenClaw chat interface. When `ui.mathRendering` is set to `\"katex\"`, LaTeX math expressions (both inline `$...$` and display `$$...$$`) are rendered as beautifully formatted math in chat messages.\n\n## Changes\n\n### Configuration\n- Add `mathRendering?: \"off\" | \"katex\"` to `types.openclaw.ts` UI config\n- Add corresponding Zod schema in `zod-schema.ts` (inside `.strict()` ui object)\n- Add `ui.mathRendering` label in `schema.labels.ts`, help text in `schema.help.ts`, documentation in `configuration-reference.md`\n\n### Core Rendering\n- New `ui/src/ui/katex-renderer.ts` module with math extraction, pre-processing, and synchronous rendering\n- Placeholder-based architecture: extract math Ôćĺ sanitize HTML Ôćĺ restore rendered math\n- Handles `\\$` escaped delimiters, nested braces, display/inline modes\n- Post-processes `katex-error` class Ôćĺ falls back to raw LaTeX text\n- CJK boundary support: `isCJKBoundary()` covers fullwidth punctuation, CJK punctuation, CJK ideographs, Hangul, Kana\n\n### DOMPurify Integration\n- New `toSanitizedMarkdownHtmlWithKatex()` function (original `toSanitizedMarkdownHtml` unchanged)\n- `uponSanitizeAttribute` DOMPurify hook using `node.closest(\".katex\")` for attribute preservation\n- Extended allowed tags: 29 MathML + SVG tags (msqrt, mroot, msubsup, menclose, etc.)\n- Extended allowed attributes: 22 MathML + SVG attributes (mathvariant, displaystyle, etc.)\n\n### Rendering Pipeline\n- `grouped-render.ts`: Thread `mathRendering` through `renderMarkdownContent` selector and `renderStreamingGroup`\n- Streaming: `mathRendering` passed through `renderStreamingGroup()` Ôćĺ `renderGroupedMessage()`\n- `chat.ts`: Preload KaTeX module + CSS when `mathRendering === \"katex\"` (one-shot guard to prevent render loops)\n- 7-file bootstrap chain: `control-ui-contract.ts` Ôćĺ `control-ui.ts` Ôćĺ `control-ui-bootstrap.ts` Ôćĺ `app-view-state.ts` Ôćĺ `app.ts` Ôćĺ `app-render.ts` Ôćĺ `chat.ts`\n\n### Tests\n- 56 test cases in `katex-renderer.test.ts` covering extraction, rendering, escaping, error handling, CJK boundaries, maxSize cap\n- All 1599 UI tests pass, 3 pre-existing failures unrelated to this PR\n\n### Dependencies\n- Pinned `katex@0.16.47` (exact version, zero behavioral impact)\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n- **Full synchronous architecture**: No async changes to `toSanitizedMarkdownHtml`; new sync `toSanitizedMarkdownHtmlWithKatex` function\n- **Streaming safety**: KaTeX rendering now flows through streaming path via `mathRendering` parameter\n- **CJK boundary support**: Closing `$` before fullwidth punctuation, CJK characters, Hangul, and Kana is recognized as valid boundary\n- **Error resilience**: KaTeX parse errors gracefully fall back to displaying raw LaTeX; `maxSize: 100` prevents layout-breaking output\n- **Render loop guard**: `katexPreloadTriggered` one-shot boolean prevents infinite update cycles\n- **Zero breakage**: All existing callers of `toSanitizedMarkdownHtml` continue working unchanged\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed**: KaTeX math rendering in OpenClaw Control UI chat. Inline and display LaTeX formulas render correctly. CJK boundary formulas like `$x^2$šÜäňÇ╝` and `$E=mc^2$´╝î` also render correctly. Streaming path now passes `mathRendering` through to the renderer.\n\n**Real environment tested**: OpenClaw Control UI dev server (`pnpm dev:ui:mock`) with `mathRendering: \"katex\"` enabled, tested in Chrome browser on Linux.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after the patch**:\n1. Set `mathRendering: \"katex\"` in mock dev config\n2. Run `pnpm dev:ui:mock` to start OpenClaw UI dev server\n3. Open Chrome, navigate to `http://localhost:3010`\n4. Send chat messages containing LaTeX formulas: `$E=mc^2$`, `$$\\int_0^1 f(x)dx$$`, `$x^2$šÜäňÇ╝`, `$E=mc^2$´╝îń╗ąňĆŐ`\n5. Observe rendered output in chat window\n\n**Evidence after fix**: Screenshots from real OpenClaw UI showing correct rendering:\n\nInline and display math rendering:\n![Inline and display math](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/85a4a034-b275-4510-8d19-f66b9cf4b03e)\n\nComplex formulas (matrices, integrals, nested):\n![Complex formulas](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2a75c1c0-50de-4452-a862-fd16e2d27936)\n\nCJK boundary formulas (fullwidth comma, CJK ideograph):\n![CJK boundary formulas](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/98b80524-6179-4e3a-af53-7f36ea766e51)\n\nAdditional formula rendering (fractions, roots, Greek letters):\n![Additional formulas](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/650da05c-14e0-4b5d-ab21-79022feadcfb)\n\n**Observed result after fix**: All LaTeX formulas render correctly in the OpenClaw chat interface ÔÇö inline math, display math, complex nested formulas, and CJK boundary cases. KaTeX CSS loads correctly, no raw LaTeX visible, no red error messages, no layout issues.\n\n**What was not tested**: Actual AI model integration (requires API key). Multi-session switching while KaTeX is loaded. Very long formula chains that might trigger maxSize fallback.\n\n",
